:QUOTE [subtitle:Cormac McCarthy, quotetype:PLAIN]
Each the other's world entire. That is all they had and it was enough.

:JOURNEY
Rereading The Road
Read
Impact
- First read at 26 | 4 | Devastating literature | Their bond rendered with real beauty
- Reread at 38 | 5 | Physically painful | Every scene with the boy different as a parent
- Carrying the fire | 5 | More true on reread | The metaphor sharpens with what you know
- The ending | 5 | Only intensified | Same impact across reads, stronger the second time

